main event: A civilian reported observing a star-like object hovering and then disappearing behind a tree in Fairborn, Ohio on 17 September 1966.
interesting points: The witness saw the object which was white and about half the size of a basketball,The object hovered for about 1 minute before moving quickly and disappearing,The sighting lasted a total of 5 minutes, indicating the possibility of aircraft activity around that time,The report suggests the object may have been a particular aircraft making a low-level approach prior to landing,No photographs were included in the report.
